Program: Last Word
Title: BB King, Kenan Evren, Sir Maurice Flanagan, Maya Plisetskaya, Wally Kahn
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b05tpz76
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 17 May 2015
Matthew Bannister on B.B. King whose blues guitar took him from the cotton fields of Mississippi to international stardom. Kenan Evran the Turkish general who took power in a military coup in 1980 and was later sentenced to life imprisonment. Sir Maurice Flanagan who took Emirates Airlines from a two plane cargo operation to a multi billion dollar business. The Soviet ballet star Maya Plisetskaya And the glider pilot Wally Kahn who campaigned to make Lasham - an ex RAF base in Hampshire - into a world beating gliding club. Show less